cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with maximum likelihood estimation for discrete energy-based models, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses results from asymptotic theory, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with statistical efficiency, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
